import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['home_score'])
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Home Score')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['goal_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    plt.hist(data['goal_difference'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['goal_difference'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['goal_difference'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Goal Difference')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of goal difference?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['goal_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    avg_goal_diff = data.groupby('division')['goal_difference'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_goal_diff['division'], avg_goal_diff['goal_difference'], color=np.random.rand(3,))
    ax.axhline(y=avg_goal_diff['goal_difference'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Goal Difference')
    ax.set_xlabel('Division')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Goal Difference')
    ax.set_title('What is the average goal difference for each division?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['date'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['home_score'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Home Score')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of home scores over time?')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
    ax.axhline(y=data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Home Score')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
